translated: Fremer, Sven Albdn, 'sitatdisingenjöir, Nybro', born on May 1st, 1893 in Främmestad, Skåne. He married An ma-Lisa Palmqvist in 1928 and they had two children, Björn born in 1929 and Eddii born in 1941. He graduated from CTI (VoV) and worked as a technical engineer from 1916-1920, then worked in the colonial government in the Dutch East Indies from 1920-1924, before returning to Sweden to work for the provincial government of Celebes until 1934. From 1935, he worked in Nybro as a director. He was the chairman of the Nybro local home association from 1938. His hobbies included ethnography and folklore research (he donated an ethnographic collection from the Sunda Islands to his hometown museum).
